Actually, I agree that we should help out our fellow man.  However, I believe that a corporate executive owes his loyalty to the stockholders, not the employees (and the law states this as well).  I believe, from a religious perspective, that we should help our fellow men.  I don't think the government should be involved in this when it can be avoided though.  I believe in the absolute maximum privatization of the government, with only a few functions being retained such as national defense and law enforcement.  Social programs should be administered through the private sector. <br>
