I don't blame people for being laid off.  I never said it was their fault.  All I said is that it was never represented to them that the company would employ them indefinitely.  The deal was for at will employment, and that's what they got.  The employee can leave at any time and the company can fire him at any time.<br>
<br>
Why can't these people just get other jobs?  I have seen *many* people laid off.  They go out job hunting and get another job.  Sometimes it's not as good as the one they lost, sometimes it's better, but they don't cry about how horrible life is.  They get back out there and keep going.  That is part of life.  Life has ups and downs, and we are responsible for dealing with them.  The government is not your mommy.  Its job is not to care for you.  Its job is to enforce law, provide for national defense, etc.  It's YOUR job to care for yourself and your family.  If the neighborhood can no longer support the jobs, then the people should move somewhere that can.  That's how life works.<br>
<br>
Basically, I'm sick of the mentality that we are all helpless and need the government to care for us from cradle to grave.  How about taking a bit of personal responsibility and taking care of yourself?  That's the way it should be.  I'm all for *private* charities helping out with those that have experienced some bad luck.  However, I believe every person should be able to pick and choose his charities and causes and not be forced to give his money to the government to mismanage or waste on pork barrel spending projects to get senators and representatives elected.  (Both parties are very guilty of this!)<br>
