Basically everything in this thread is contained in an economics 101 course, nothing discussed is difficult by any means, and is quite logical.<br>
<br>
The government nor the businesses involved w/ lay-offs are responsible for holding anyones hands into their next line of employment.  There are so many ways of staying a-float if you're laid off in this country.  <br>
