<br>
Back in the early 90's when we had a little recession, my parents had just bought a new house and ran up some debt.  My mother (primary source of income in our household because my dad is a lazy bastage) was layed off due to the distribution center she worked at being closed.  My parents were forced to file bankrupcy, my mother found a job that paid about 5/8's what she was making at her last job, but that kept us afloat and it also kept us in our house and nothing reposessed.<br>
<br>
That's one example of just our circumstance, it does not by any means apply to everyone, but whenever I get worried about not making enough money to support myself or my wife, or getting laid off, I just think back at my parents and realize, they lived through it, there's absolutely no reason I shouldn't either.<br>
