<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=440005" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:georgia;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Graph's toys</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1749<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/03 10:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another thing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Unemployment is paid by the company, not the government.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sort of true.  The company that lays you off does not pay you unemployment.  The government does.  However, it's funded by taxes paid on payroll I think.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I take that as screw you if you can't keep up.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It simply expresses the futility of attempting to stop progress.  You just can't do it.  Even the most powerful of forces, such as the Catholic Church during the renaissance, tried to stand in the way of scientific progress, and failed miserably.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There is a low rate of drop outs in my hometown. So most people have at least a high school education.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's good, then they should be able to get jobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have moved for jobs also. But the majority of people affected have roots there. You know, roots, have owned their home for 10-15 years, have a church they regularly attend, friends, their kids have their friends, famliy that lives close by. So it's fine with you if a whole community goes down the drain. We've established that. I'm not going to debate this point with you anymore.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sure, it sucks that some people might have to move.  I feel bad for them that such things happen, but it's part of life.  I don't like that the community goes down the drain and that people have to move, but I certainly do not think it's fair to expect a company to do something that is unprofitable so that the employees don't have to move, especially when those same employees would gladly ditch the company and take new jobs if they got better offers for more money.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=misscheivous>MissCheivous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/10/03 1:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another thing</span><hr size=1> Ugh..ok I'm done with this topic...you just don't see my point.<br>
<br>
The companies stayed in business just fine before they left. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.comcast.net/~dremarian/wsb/media/68398/site1036.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=440005" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:georgia;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Graph's toys</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1752<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/10/03 2:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another thing</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The companies stayed in business just fine before they left.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, but the decisions they make will lead to greater profitability, and achieving greater profitability is the job of corporate executives.  That's what they are required by law to seek.  If they make a decision that reduces profitability, they aren't doing their jobs.<br>
<br>
Compassion and loyalty certainly have a place in this world.  However, that place is not business.  Business is just that, it's about making money.  It's not personal and it has nothing to do with compassion.  If you want warmth and friendship, go to your family, your friends, your church, your shrink, etc.  Don't go to a corporation.<br>
<br>
They hire you to perform a service.  The terms of the employment contract you sign the day you join represent a mutual agreement as to your employment.  If they don't specify in the employment contract that they have some obligation to you, and you sign it, you agree to work for them with the understanding that they do not have that obligation to you.<br>
<br>
Your understanding of the role of corporations in your life and the lives of others is skewed and unrealistic.  Their role is not to care for you or take care of you in any way.  They bear no responsibility for your happiness or for the fulfillment of your dreams.  There is a quid pro quo relationship between you, you provide services, they provide cash, and that's it.  Nothing more.  If you read more into the relationship, you are reading into it something that is not and was never designed to be there.<br>
<br>
Going to a corporation and expecting some sort of compassion or loyalty is like calling your credit card company for marriage counseling.  It's just not in the job description, and it's entirely inappropriate to expect it of them.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=168.topic&start=81&stop=92>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=168.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=168.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.threadControl?topicID=168.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=168.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=168.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email n